inn1.comm: wide outside the off stump, Dravid mistimes the cut through cover to the deep, picks up two runs, off the mark
taps it gently to the on side and takes a quick single
good ball bit wide outside the off stump, swinging away, Tendulkar watchfully lets it go through
good ball once again in the corridor, lets it go through, good carry to the keeper
short of length outside the off stump, moves away, Sachin opens the face off the bat, the ball goes past the slips to thirdman fence, ball kept low, well adjusted by Sachin
gets in line and works well to fine leg
short one dug in, goes over the batsmen, signalled wide
Dropped! lovely delivery moves away after pitching, gets the edge, Carlton Baugh drops it, diving to his right.
good length delivery in the corridor, Tendulkar watchfully lets it go
short in length, looking to work it through the on side, misses, strikes high on the pad and drops on the track, Edwards quickly fields on his follow-through
pitched up, driven straight back down the track, strikes the stumps, unlucky there not to get some runs.
beats the bat, wonderful delivery, seams away after pitching, draws him to play at that
works it front of square leg in the gap to pick up an easy single
full and on the legs, asking for trouble, Dravid neatly works it off his legs to midwicket fence, wonderful shot
drifting on the pads, deftly worked to fine leg to pick up an easy single
short in length and again down the leg side, tucked away behind square leg to pick up another single
bad line once again, down the leg side, signalled wide
good ball this time, looking to work through the on side, gets a thickish edge along the ground to square leg
was looking to force it through the off side, well adjusted by Sachin to drop it to the off side
nicely played, moves back and whips it through midwicket, the ball races along into the fence
down the leg side, signalled wide
moves forward and lets the ball go, strikes the pad but outside the line of the off stump, a stifled appeal from the bowler and fielders, turned down by umpire Benson
fuller delivery outside the off stump, driven firmly to mid off
good delivery pitched in line and straightens, Dravid adjust well and plays it to the off side
bad line from Edwards, drifts down leg, he oversteps too,  Dravid fails to get a bat, off the pad to fine leg fence
lets the ball go outside the off stump, good ball in the corridor, just short of length
moves forward in line and defends well to the off side
neatly opens the face off the bat and runs it down past the gully region to thirdman
again Tendulkar finds the stumps at the non-striker's end, pushed back down the track
gets a thickish edge along the ground to thirdman, Dravid was looking to drive through the off side in front of the wicket
Edwards oversteps, a tight call, works it nicely through midwicket to the deep
short and wide outside the off stump, Tendulkar moves back and slashes it over the backward-point to the fence, wonderful shot
oh.. the ball rolls along the ground after pitching, variable bounce there, lucky the ball was not in line.
fuller delivery driven to mid on
gets behind it nicely and works to midwicket
in line with the delivery, Tendulkar pushes to mid on
good delivery on a length, Dravid drops it down on the track
short in length outside the off stump, opens the face off the bat and runs it down to thirdman for a single
short delivery dug in, goes for the hook, gets a top edge and ball goes into the fine leg fence, almost goes over the fence.
width outside the off stump, Tendulkar cuts hard, the edge goes over the slips to thirdman fence.
works it neatly past the square leg umpire to the deep to pick up an easy single
Dravid goes for the pull past the square leg umpire to the deep, not a well timed shot
short in length, Dravid right behind it drops it to the on side
short ball, Dravid goes for the pull, drops short of the square leg fielder.
defends back down the track
tucks it down to fine leg to pick up an easy single
good ball, bit more bounce, Tendulkar drops his wrist and plays it down, that surprised Tendulkar
gets behind the delivery and works to Gayle at short midwicket
starts off with a wide down the leg side, brings up the 50 for India
forces off the back foot to extra-cover
nicely placed in front of square leg in the gap to pick up the single
good line from Bradshaw angled across past Dravid, lets it go through to Carlton Baugh
moves back in line and forces to backward-point
turns it around to square leg
taps it softly to the off side beside the track and they take a quick single, Dravid and Chanderpaul collide, they seem to be okay.
forces off the back foot past the backward-point to the deep, thirdman runs around and fields the ball, Taylor oversteps
punches to point, not a well timed shot
short in length, Dravid gets on top off it and plays it well past the backward-point to the deep, before the thirdman runs around to field it, they pick up two runs
a beauty from Taylor, pitches and moves away, Dravid drawn forward to play at that, lovely delivery
gets the edge along the ground past the slips to thirdman fence, a tentative defense from Dravid

Oh ouch.. that hurt him, the ball takes off after pitching, strikes the glove, that was nasty, Dravid quickly drops his bat and removes the gloves and looks at his finger, the Physio runs in to attend him
worked to the on side, fielded by Gayle at short midwicket
pushes wide of mid on to pick up a single
drops his wrist and works to square leg
moves forward in line and pushes to mid off, who is a bit deep, they take the single
good ball angled across, Tendulkar moves in line and lets it go through to Carlton Baugh
looking to work it through the on side, misses it, strikes the pad and rolls down the track
good ball on a good length, Tendulkar works to the on side
lovely shot from Dravid, drives on the up through the gap to cover fence, wonderful timing
good comeback from Taylor, the ball comes back in, Dravid drops it to the off side
lets the ball go outside the off stump
works to midwicket
good shot but no runs this time, forces off the back foot to backward-point, straight to the fielder
moves back and plays it back down the track, fielded by Taylor on his follow-through
gets an edge on to the pad and then goes to the off side, was looking to work it through the on side
lovely shot from Tendulkar, it was in the slot outside the off stump, drives it well in the gap between extra-cover and mid off, the ball races into the fence
covers the line and lets the ball go through, it was angled across him
gets behind the ball and defends to the off side
looking to play to the on side, misses it, hit high on the pad
drives through the line to covers, cannot find the gap, hit straight to the fielder
starts off with a wide, swings away, Baugh fails to collect it cleanly
short in length this time, Tendulkar gets behind it and defends back down the track.
wonderful delivery, short in length, moves away after pitching, Tendulkar on the back foot plays at it, beats the bat

a nasty delivery, jumps up off the track, strikes the glove off Tendulkar, that took off, lucky the ball did not carry to any fielder close by, Tendulkar looks to be injured. The ball struck the little finger of the top hand.
left alone outside the off stump
comes forward to a good length delivery and defends to the on side
this rolls along the ground, it was short in length, uneven bounce, the bowler and batsman have a laugh.
works it nicely behind square leg to pick up a single
gets behind in line and defends to the off side
deftly works behind square leg to pick up a single
looking to force it through the off side, not a well timed shot
looking to play to the on side, strikes the pad, they scamper through for a leg bye to square leg
Tendulkar defends, gets an edge and the ball gets trapped inside the pads

Smith gets Dravid, good ball angled in, it was short in length and it kept a bit low, Dravid caught in the crease looking to play to the on side, misses the line, strikes the pad, loud shout goes up, given by umpire Benson, first break through for West Indies
banged in short, Pathan ducks under it, a welcome delivery from Smith
moves forward in line and pushes to the on side
Pathan flashes hard on the front foot, gets the edge in the air past the slips to thirdman fence
another delivery that takes off after pitching, Pathan takes his eye off the ball, takes it on the body
drives on the up, beats the bat, lovely delivery from Smith angled across
lovely shot from Tendulkar after the break, driven dead straight down the track over the stumps to the fence
another shot driven on the up to the off side, not a well timed shot
gets behind the ball and defends to the on side
good ball, Tendulkar plays from the crease, back down the track
uses his feet this time, gets an inside edge on to the track, making the bowler think
this time waits in the crease and works it neatly to fine leg to pick up a single
mistimes the cut to the off side, did not get on top off it
short in length, Tendulkar forces to the off side
looking to play to the on side, misses it, off the pad they go through for a leg bye to square leg
punches it to mid off
drives in the air past the slips to thirdman, a thickish edge
keeps low outside the off stump, Tendulkar looking to drive through the off side, misses it
played through midwicket to the deep, comes back for the second run, the out-field has become slow
looking to play to the on side, misses it, strikes the pad and falls on the off side
moves back and punches to mid off
short in length, Tendulkar stands tall and defends to the off side
good delivery angled across, Tendulkar looking to run it down, gets beaten, through to Carlton Baugh
nicely played, worked well in front of square leg to the deep, comes back for the second run
cut away to thirdman for a single
That is maximum! short ball, Tendulkar quickly on the back foot pulls it well in the air over the square leg fence into the stands, wonderful strike
works it to the on side to pick up a single
moves back and pushes to point
it was short and wide, Pathan cuts hard in the air to cover fence
this time pitches it up, driven straight back, well fielded by Smith on his follow-through
poor fielding at fine leg, tucked away nicely around the corner to fine leg, bad fielding there allows a boundary, brings up 50 for Sachin, well played.
defended to the on side
gets in line and defends well to the off side
short delivery down the leg side, Tendulkar misses the pull shot, off Tendulkar's glove or hand, drops just short of Carlton Baugh
defended to the off side
looking to play to the on side, misses it, off the pad to the on side
gets behind the delivery and blocks it to the off side
moves forward and drives to mid off, Tendulkar took off, Pathan makes a quick call of Wait.
good shot, Pathan cuts hard in the air wide of thirdman to the fence, there was width there
good ball short in length, tucks up Pathan, no room, drops it on the track
a miscued shot from Pathan, looking to pull, gets it high on the bat and the ball falls safely behind the wicket at the non-striker's end, they scamper through for a single
opens the face off the bat and steers it down to thirdman, a cheeky shot from Tendulkar
works it nicely to fine leg, played it late, Taylor runs around and makes a fine stop, saves two runs
gets behind it and opens the face off the bat and plays to backward-point
turns it around in front of square leg, the fielder quickly gets around it to prevent any single
tucks it off his hips behind square leg to the deep to pick up an easy single
bit wide outside the off stump, Tendulkar waits for it and runs it down to thirdman to pick up a single
pushes firmly to mid on and calls Tendulkar through for a quick single, well run
good ball short in length, no room for Pathan, blocks it to the on side
bit wide outside the off stump, kept a bit low, gets the bottom edge, falls well short of Carlton Baugh, Pathan was looking for the big drive.
played to the sweeper cover to pick up a single
moves back in line and works it nicely to the vacant square leg to pick up a single
pushes with and angled bat to point, well fielded
fuller delivery outside the off stump, Pathan pushes to mid on
a beauty angled across, Tendulkar moves forward and looks to play to the on side, beats the bat through to Carlton Baugh, a stifled appeal for caught behind
driven through the covers in the gap to deep to pick up couple of runs
pushes firmly back down the track
room outside the off stump, Tendulkar cuts hard to the sweeper cover for a single
punched to mid off on the front foot
Pathan has a go at it, miscues it to deep midwicket, gets couple of runs, good fielding there
fast and quick on a good length, Tendulkar pushes gently to mid on and takes off for a quick single
down the leg side, signalled wide
good ball banged in short, Pathan drops his wrist and plays it down, well played
a mishit from Pathan, it was in the slot, driven straight past the bowler to long on fence
looking to play through the on side, gets a leading edge to the off side
moves in line and opens the face off the bat and runs it down to thirdman
tucks it around the corner to fine leg to pick up an easy single
Wham! In the slot, he just swings that golf-style with a fine followthrough and hits it straight down the ground for maximum!
swings down the pads and its called wide, bad ball
rank full toss on the pads, easily flicked past square leg
short of a good length on the stumps, chopped into the covers
this one's banged in shorter, Pathan steps back and flays the bat at it, basically helping it on its way, and the ball goes high, high up and disappears over third man for six, top shot!
fuller on off, he drives at it and gets bat onto it, the ball trickles towards point and they scamper through for one, Sachin really wanted that run
good ball, lands around off and moves into him as he tries to cheekily run it down to third man, beaten comprehensively by the swing
full and swinging in again, driven straight to short cover
and he's picked for runs first ball, this one lands on off and Pathan makes room to cut, gets bat onto it and sneaks that past the man at deep gully for four
better ball, flighted on middle and off and he defends off the backfoot
fuller on middle and leg, easily driven towards mid-on for a single
good ball on the stumps, watchfully defended back to the bowler
good ball again, middle and leg, he looks to drive but falls over in his stride
short of a good length on off, driven to covers off the backfoot
fuller this time and its pushed into the covers, well fielded by Gayle there
wider of offstump this time, Pathan reaches out and guides that on its way past gully and backward point and picks up his fifth ODI fifty, the experiment, if we can still call it that, pays off here
good length ball outside off, he keeps that down towards third man and gets down to the other side
short delivery on middle and off, he gets a rush of blood and backs away, looks to smash that through covers but only finds Gayle again
dropped in short again, this time he swivels and pulls that to square leg
tossed up on middle and leg, he advances and drives that hard towards mid-on
Shot! Dropped in short, and quick, but he makes room and carves that behind point for four, his first boundary in ten overs
middle and leg, tucked to the man at square leg
middle and leg again, he easily drives that past short midwicket and scurries through, calls again as the sweeper comes in and gets two, well run
agains this is full and he taps it to mid-wicket and gets one
middle and off, he looks to play it to leg but gets hit on the pads and the ball rolls towards the offside, scampers through for one anyways
fuller on leg stump, tucked towards square leg for one
full on leg stumps, he looks to flick that but the ball thuds off the pads and races away past a diving Baugh and down to fine leg, fielder comes around and cuts it off but they steal two
width and he goes for a fierce cut, just gets the toe of the bat on it but theres enough to see that fly down to third man for four
outside off, looks to cut but mistimes towards point, ball sort of stopped there on the off side
fuller on off, he leans into and square drives that straight to point
good length delivery on off, no real movement on that as Sachin goes back and runs that to point, he was hurried into that shot
tossed up on middle and leg, he gives him the charge but can only drive to mid-on
short on off and its cut into the covers for one
going down leg and he looks to sweep but the ball runs away for leg-byes
good ball on the stumps, spins away as he tries to get bat on it
middle and leg and its tucked around the corner for one more
tossed up on off, he just goes back and taps that in front of square and sets off for an easy single to retain strike
good ball on the stumps, he goes back and defends but the ball rolls towards point
half-volley on middle and off, driven to Hinds at long-on for a single
shot! Full delivery outside off and its driven fiercely through the offside, ball slows down as it reaches the ropes and the sweeper sends it back in
good ball on middle and leg and its tucked straight towards midwicket
close call there! Well-directed slower ball, that dangerous Bravo yorker again, he steps away and looks to hit to the off, but the result is a French-cut past the 'keeper to fine leg for four
leg stump, flicked fine for a single
good length ball on off, punched back to Gayle off the backfoot
fuller on middle, driven past mid-on for a single
flighted on middle and leg, he looks to paddle-sweep that but can only find the man at backward square leg
tossed up on off, driven to covers for one
a quicker ball, off stump, tries to cut but gets a leg-bye past the 'keeper instead
off stump, goes back and defends
full on off, well driven to mid-off for one
rank half-volley on the stumps and he unleashes that majestic flick through mid-wicket, subtle roll of the wrists and all, and gets four all the way, top shot
wow, some bounce on that one as it lands on off and just rears off a sweet spot, Sachin ducks out of the way in surprise
fuller and it keeps a bit low, Sachin looks to run it down but misses
good length on off, he dabs that past point and gets one, well played
strives for that yorker again, not as well-directed as last time, Pathan stands and drives that into the offside
full on middle and off, driven towards mid-on to bring up the 200 for India
on the stumps, driven back to Gayle

gone this time! Relative straight ball on the stumps, he makes room to carve that through the offside but gets an inside edge on the base of the stumps, furniture disturbed, Gayle gets the vital breakthrough and Pathan has to go for a well-made 64
on off, driven into the covers
on off again, changed the pace on that one, Sehwag hurries and defends
tossed up again, and  its defended back to the bowler, good tidy over from Gayle, picked up the dangerous Pathan too
full on off, leans into it and dabs that to the left of point and calls for the run
full and wide off off, he throws everything at that and misses it completely, trying too much too soon?
this lands outside off and nips in, he uses the soft hands to run that down to third man and get his first run of the day
he'll get four this time, opened the blade on that one and ran it down past a diving Baugh, well played sir
oh-ho, another ripper that just kicks from off and has him going down on his haunches to get out of harm's way
Take that! In the slot outside  off, he frees the arms and drives that over mid-off for four more, classic shot
middle and leg, driven to mid-on
middle and leg again, tucked fine for two, well run
shorter on off, he goes back and flicks that to square for another run
shorter on middle and leg, he goes back and works that to mid-on for one
again middle and leg, works that to the onside, wants two but will have to settle for one, he's on 99, can you believe, in his comeback match!

there it is! Full on middle and leg, and for the umpteenth time we see the genius just step across the stumps and turn that to square leg for a hundred, crowd loves it and thats century number 40 for him, incredible innings for him in his first full match back in the side
dropped short and he steps back and uppercuts that way over the 'keeper for six, typical Sehwag shot!

Gone! Full on the stumps, it keeps very low and skids through him close to the ankles and shatter the stumps, bowler looks almost sheepish with that wicket but Sehwag has to go for 9, what an over here
this one lands on a good length and nips back into him, hits him high on the kneeroll, maybe an inside edge there
another good, quick ball on the stumps as him going back and defending into the covers, loud shout of 'NO' there
attempts the yorker, more of a low fulltoss in the end, its driven down to wide of mid-on for one and Dhoni's off the mark
middle and leg again, tucked off the pads but right to square leg
off stump, driven to the off side
slighly shorter on off, goes back and drives to point for one
shorter and moving down leg, walks across the stumps and plays it to square leg
quicker and he can only go back and play it back to the bowler, Gayle mixing it up well here, taking the pace of the ball does work
good quick ball outside off,  too good for him as he misses the dab to third man
middle and leg, turns and dabs that into the ground in front of mid-wicket
good ball on the stumps, Dhoni goes back and drives to cover

and he's bowled! Like the one to Sehwag, this one just shoots under his bat and hits the base of middle and off, he just could not adjust to that one, can't blame him too, India have lost their fourth wicket, Taylor picks up another
full toss and all he can do is play it back to the bowler
full on the stumps, played to the onside
middle and leg, worked past mid-wicket for one, thought about the second but refrained
offstump line, driven in the gap between covers and mid-off
beaten by the low bounce outside off
good length ball on the stumps, defended back to the bowler's right
full on off, driven to mid-off and they scamper through for a run, well run that
full on leg stump, he goes to flick it fine but that ball carries off the pads for four, legbyes signalled
good length ball outside off, steered down to third man, he'll retain the strike
middle and leg line, walks across the stumps and turns it to square leg
tossed up, middle and leg again, driven down to long-on
good ball on the stumps, played back to Gayle
tossed up on leg, flicked through square leg, used his feet and changed his shot at the last minute
this one's turned in front of mid-wicket, well run
turned off the pads to mid-wicket for one, again he'll keep strike
good ball, the yorker, well dug out in the end
full outside off, looks to cream that past covers but mistimes that and chops it into the ground
leg stump and its tucked off the pads with ease for a brace, well played
good length ball on the off, driven to extra cover off the backfoot
dropped in short, useless ball, quite slow too and he hops up and smashes that over extra cover with a flat bat for four, thats the 250 up!
slower ball outside off, fuller this time, makes room to square drive but can only get one as a loose shot trickles towards point
a no-ball, they dont need that now
identical ball and this time he manages to get one to mid-on
dropped in shorter, sweeps that past square leg
advances down the track, Gayle sees him and keeps the ball short, can only drive to covers
another wide again, bad ball
full on the legs, well flicked throught mid-wicket, Chanderpaul in the deep dives well and saves a boundary
Bang! In the zone, he frees the arms and hits that hard and flat through mid-off for four
on off, can only chop that to point
full on middle and leg, worked to the man at mid-on
full on off, easily flicked through square leg for one

Dropped in short, he makes room and carves that high in the air over point, three fielders converge in the deep but the ball lands smack in the middle of them, the sweeper coming in gets to it and suddenly withdraws, a dropped chance and the bowler cant believe it
SHOT! Full on off and he leans into it and drives that over covers for six, amazing shot from Sachin
full again but all he can do is drive to cover
the yorker almost, on leg, looks to flick but gets an inside edge, balls stops at his feet
Fantastic! The Sachin of yore! Lands outside off stump, the half-volley,and its dispatched with a high-arm over mid-off again for maximum, awesome!
full on off, he changes his intentional shot and chops it to backward point
full on middle, the yorker, squeezed into the covers for a sharp single
chips this one over the bowler's head and gets one, Sachin wanted two but they dont get it, wonder who the crowd would rather see on strike...
full outside off, moves across and tries to play it to midwicket, outside edge towards point
top shot again, this one's full on the legs and he swings that over mid-on, one bounce and over the ropes for four
dropped in short, makes room and once more flat-bats that over extra cover, ball bounces in front of Fidel Edwards at deep long-off and he allows it to go past him for four, awful
Gone! Full on the legs, flicks it off the pads but can only find a diving Dwayne Smith at deep backward square leg who covers good ground and pulls off a superb diving catch, Raina goes for a good 34
bye bye birdie! Amazing! Fullish on the stumps and its just swung high over long-on for maximum for Sachin's fourth six, is he on fire or what?
beaten comprehesively by a trademark slower ball on off, fishes at it makes no contact
full outside off, begging to be hit, he drives with a flourish but will only get one down to a wide long-off, back to Sachin
another slower ball on off, tries to cheekily sweep it but makes bad contact
good job, son! Another slow yorker is driven back to Bravo, valuable over
Not this time! Maximum No. 5! Comes down the track to another slower one, frees the arms and unleashes an awesome extracover drive for six, intense!

full again and slower, as you would expect, and he drives it to cover for one, what an innings from Sachin, 142 unbeaten runs, he's stayed all through the innings to take India to 309, as super an innings in a full 50-over comeback innings as you can see, or expect, or imagine...very, very fine hundred, his 40th

inn2.comm: and he begins with a no-ball, poor
good ball, full on the stumps and its played back to the bowler
not as full and some swing away but Gayle negiotiates it off the backfoot, tapped back to Pathan's right
a no-ball, a real shocker of a full toss on off, Gayle does well to keep that down and run it past gully for one
a full, swinging delivery outside off is driven to a diving Mohammad Kaif in the covers
good length on off, does well to steer that to point
full again and its driven to covers
full on leg, tries to drive but doesnt time it well, ball sort of stops at his feet
good ball lands on a sweet spot on off and seams away, Gayle is taken by surprise and moves away
very good ball smack on the stumps, keeps low and Gayle is caught in front but just gets a thin inside edge on that one
beaten as one moves across him from middle and off, good ball
another good one lands on middle and leg and has him hopping back to defend, quicker delivery that was
fuller on middle and leg, well turned past a diving square leg and they run hard for three
full on middle and leg, he hustles into his shot and gets an inside egde between his legs for four
width offered, he stands tall and smashes that between point and cover for four, classic Gayle stroke!
full and swinging away from outside off, has a full swing but misses completely, Dhoni takes it behind the stumps
beaten again outside the off stump as that one swings away from him
a good length on off and he stands there and powerfully biffs that off the backfoot past a diving mid-off for four more, unorthodox but supreme
thats very wide outside off and duly called
good ball on middle and leg, turned to square leg
full and moving away on off, left alone with a raise of the bat
another wide, ball ball down the leg side
good comeback, beats him on the forward prod outside off stump
drifts to leg and he taps that down to fine leg for one
bad, ball ball to begin with, dropped in short and its sent over square leg for four, good aggresive shot

he's gone! Some luck there for the bowler, dropped in again very short, Chanderpaul goes for a hook, gets a top edge and it goes high down to deep fine leg, the ball is illuminated against the dark sky for some time, seems to be up for a long time and going for six, but Munaf Patel judges that well and holds a very good catch just inside the ropes and India get a breakthrough!
close! Nipped back in and hit the front leg, maybe a little high, umpire Rauf shakes his head
Streaky! Beautifully bowled on and around off, some swing, Sarwan stands there and edges  that between his feet and the stumps for four
nips back and catches him high on the knee roll as he hops in his crease, ball rolls to the offside, successful over for the bowler
some good movement outside the off, its left alone
full on off, well tapped to the offside and they call for the run
good ball on and around off, Gayle stands and chops that to point
another full and swinging ball on off, he plays from the crease and the ball shoots along the ground past gully for one
good ball on the stumps, driven back the ground off Agarkar's hand and into the nonstriker's stumps
a loose delivery outside off, chopped past backward point, Pathan moves across from third man and cuts it off, they pick up a couple anyway
angles one across him, swings wide but the umpire believes it was fine
just the slightest room outside off and its creamed between point and cover, not well-timed but the big man's power is such that he gets four!
dropped in shorter, he hops on one leg and pulls it, ball trickles down to fine leg for one
better, better, full on middle and leg, some good swing there has Sarwan caught on the crease again
moves across him, he judges the movement and leaves it alone
much wider across the stumps, Sarwan goes to flay that past point but misses, wide given
this one swings down the legs for Dhoni to take, another wide called as RP just loses it a little, he's trying to much and getting a lot of swing too
another ball on the stumps is tickled around the corner for a single
outside off and swinging away, left alone
good length ball on middle and off, he hops and defends it back to the bowler
this lands outside off, Sarwan leaves it just as the ball dips low and rolls to Dhoni, there's that lack of bounce again
very good ball, real wicket-to-wicket stuff this, Sarwan can only go back and play it back to Agarkar
wide, wide, wide - Sarwan again tries to cash in with the cut but its too far away from him
brings this one back from off but Sarwan drops the bat and steals one in front of point
shot! Fuller on off, he stands and hits that in the air over between cover and mid-off to round off the over with four to his name, stand-and-deliver approach adopted by Gayle
width outside the off and he gets the bat onto it late and chops four past where gully should have been
better ball, on the stumps, Sarwan goes back and defends
shorter in length, middle and leg line, he hops and turns it to square leg for one
drifts down leg, he goes for some sort of pull-flick but the ball raps the pads and runs away fine
outside the off stump, flashed at and it flies over Sehwag at first slip, surprised by the bounce on that one
leg stump line this time and he easily flicks that around the corner for one to keep strike
fine cut shot! Just short outside off stump and he executes a fine slap smack between cover and point
better ball, close to offstump and he defends from the crease, edge shoots along the ground to a diving gully
width offered but he misses out on the cut shot this time
swings down leg, goes for a flick, ball clips the pads and goes to Dhoni who fumbles it and gives away four legbyes
better and off the bat, identical ball on leg, this time he flicks it down for four, good shot
better ball lands on and around off and seams away, left alone by Sarwan
lands outside off and swings away, Gayle leaves it
short of a good length on middle and off, defended to the on side with a straight bat
banged in short, he doesnt quite get on top of it but has enough power to pull that past square leg for four, thats the 50 stand between these two, well played

Ouch! A full, swinging delivery on off, he gives it the kitchen sink and the ball flies high and down to deep backward point to where Agarkar misjudges it and dives too early, the ball lands in front of him, should have taken that
leg stump, flicked fine for four more
and again, leg stump and full and its mercilessly flicked over square leg for four more, Gayle in murderous mood now!
good ball to begin with, on the stumps and he defends off the backfoot
good ball on off again, played into the cover-point area off the backfoot
good ball on off, swings away from him as he hops in his crease and withdraws the bat
another full and swinging delivery outside off is left alone
full ball on off, driven back to Munaf, tidy start from the lanky fast bowler
a full delivery on the stumps is handsomely driven between bowler and nonstriker's stumps for a straight four, good shot to end a good over
good ball on middle and off, driven back to him
padded back to him again
drifts to leg, tickled to backward square leg
tossed up on middle, looks to flick but gets an edge to covers

beaten in the flight! Tossed up, a classical offbreak almost, Sarwan goes for a drive but gets beaten, Dhoni whips off the bails, stumping appeal goes upstairs but third umpire Tony Hill rightfully calls him inside the crease, but well bowled
tossed up on off again, run to point off the front foot, tidy over comes to an end
wide, drifts down the pads for Dhoni to collect, India's extras issue continues

Taken, a great catch! The big fella is surprised by the extra bounce from one on off, goes for a cut but gets a thick edge thats snapped up by Dhoni moving high and fast to his left, well held and the dangerous Gayle has to go back into the hut, Munaf strikes big time
moves across him and away from off, he leaves it alone
brings this one into him, he defends off the front foot, inside edge onto the front pad
swings away from off, good probing delivery, Lara leaves with a raise of the bat
full on off, well driven but right to Harbhajan at mid-off
a no-ball, Lara defends and squeezes this past gully for one, he's off the strike
full and swinging, Sarwan drives but gets an inside edge onto the boot, ball trickles fine and Lara wants the run
tossed up on middle and off, forward defensive from Lara
tossed up outside off, Lara sees the width and square drives that past point, on the up, for four
tossed up on off, he gets a foot forward and sweetly caresses that past mid-off for four more, majestic shot from the master batsman
quicker through the air, deceives Lara and raps him on the pads outside the line of leg stump
middle stump line, defended back to Harbhajan
full on off stump, driven to covers
full on off again, he stands there and drives that through covers for four runs, classy stroke from him
beaten in half by one that seams on off and goes past the bat
a no-ball doesnt help India's cause any
good ball on the stumps, defended back to Munaf
slightly short outside off but he mistimes the cut and hits it to point
tossed up on middle and off, defended to the on side, bowler fields it
wide of the pads and duly called
Beats everyone down the leg side and runs away for four
ripper on off, turn and bounce, beats Lara on the drive
good ball on middle and off, turned fine but no run there
quicker ball on middle and leg has him going back and defending
again drifts to leg and its worked around the corner for a sharp single
seams away from a full length on off, Lara shoulders arms
good ball on the stumps, driven into covers
Close shave! He shoulders arms to one that lands on off and jags in very close to off stump
better length, fuller and he stands and turns that towards mid-wicket
full and swinging on off, goes for an expansive drive that rolls to mid-wicket
good ball, turns from off, Sarwan hops and defends and the ball takes the edge past slip
turns this one from middle to square leg, almost a mix-up between the batsmen but they make it home in the end, not a very good thrown there
and we have another needless wide down the legs

Superb! Glorious! Lara uses the feet well and dances down the track, collects that on the pitch and hoists it dead straight between long-off and long-on for six, it sails out of the ground, talk about fantastic sixes!
shorter on off, punched to mid-off
tossed up on off again, Lara drives on the up in the gap at mid-off for four runs, good shot
full on off but driven to cover on the rise
swings into him, rapped on the pad but looked to be legside, they pinch a run
full on the off, driven to covers
middle and leg, tapped to square leg
good length on middle and off, turned to the on side but no run
full, too full and he leans into it with a sublime drive between the stumps and mid-off, ball meets the ropes in a flash, awesome stroke
and he leaves this one as it nips back and comes quite close to off, he knows where his stumps are, it appears
